column2: Популярные напитки оказались путем к онкологии и болезням сердца
column5: Доктор Александр Мясников в эфире канала "Россия 1" рассказал, что в компотах и морсах содержится очень много сахара, а от алкоголя и вовсе лучше воздержаться. Но больше всего вреда человеку может нанести сладкая разноцветная газировка.

column5: NASA is updating its coverage of the upcoming launch and docking activities for the agency’s SpaceX Crew-3 mission with astronauts to the International Space Station.

column2: NASA, National Geographic Partner to Show Inside Artemis Moon Mission
column5: NASA has selected National Geographic to help tell the story of Artemis II, the first Artemis flight that will carry astronauts around the Moon and back to Earth aboard the agency’s Orion spacecraft.

column2: NASA’s Juno: Science Results Offer First 3D View of Jupiter Atmosphere
column5: New findings from NASA’s Juno probe orbiting Jupiter provide a fuller picture of how the planet’s distinctive and colorful atmospheric features offer clues about the unseen processes below its clouds.

column2: NASA to Host Briefing on Webb Telescope Engineering, Deployments
column5: NASA will hold a virtual media briefing 11 a.m. EDT Tuesday, Nov. 2, to discuss the engineering of the James Webb Space Telescope, the world’s largest and most powerful space science telescope.

column2: NASA Invites Media to Learn About S-MODE Mission
column5: NASA will hold a media teleconference at 1:30 p.m. EDT Friday, Oct. 29 to share information about the Sub-Mesoscale Ocean Dynamics Experiment (S-MODE), a campaign to study small ocean whirlpools, eddies, and currents.

column2: NASA to Host Briefing to Reveal New Findings from Jupiter’s Atmosphere
column5: NASA will hold a virtual media briefing at 3 p.m. EDT Thursday, Oct. 28, to discuss the latest results from the agency’s Juno spacecraft.

column2: NASA Invites Media to Launch of IXPE Mission to Study X-rays in Space
column5: Media accreditation is open for the upcoming launch of NASA’s Imaging X-ray Polarimetry Explorer (IXPE) mission, which will measure polarized X-rays from exotic cosmic objects, such as black holes and neutron stars, to better understand these types of phenomena and extreme environments.

column2: NASA Commits $28 Million to Underfunded US Jurisdictions
column5: NASA has awarded $28 million to fund the next five years of research infrastructure development across 28 jurisdictions.

column2: NASA Completes Mega-Moon Rocket Stacking, Invites Media to Learn More
column5: NASA has completed stacking of the agency’s mega-Moon rocket and spacecraft that will launch the next generation of deep space operations, including Artemis missions on and around the Moon.

column5: NASA will provide coverage of the upcoming prelaunch and launch activities for the agency’s SpaceX Crew-3 mission with astronauts to the International Space Station.
